{c:'HYD',t:'Schematic line types',d:'Solid = working pressure. Long-dashed = pilot/control. Short-dashed = drain. Bend in line = flexible hose.'},
{c:'PNEU',t:'FRL order',d:'Filter \u2192 Regulator \u2192 Lubricator (inlet to outlet). Filter first removes water/particles. Lubricator last so oil reaches equipment.'},
{c:'PNEU',t:'Double vs single-acting',d:'Double: air powers both strokes (needs 4-way valve). Single: air one way, spring returns \u2014 simpler but limited retraction force.'},
